> A signature Donn Beach drink built on his trademark Pernod-and-bitters secret combination — the same Don's Mix DNA that runs through the Zombie and Cobra's Fang.[^1][^2]
>
> Brand recommendations. Best: Smith & Cross or Hamilton Pot Still Black for the dark Jamaican; Don Q Añejo or Bacardi Heritage Limited Edition for the light Puerto Rican; Cointreau; Pernod (proper); BG Reynolds falernum. Economical: Appleton Estate 8 or Coruba; Plantation 3 Stars or Don Q Cristal; Combier Triple Sec; Pernod or Herbsaint; Velvet Falernum.

In a #shaker{} combine @fresh lime juice{0.5%oz}, @falernum{0.5%oz}, @Pernod{0.125%tsp}, @Angostura bitters{1%dash}, @Cointreau{3%tsp}, @light Puerto Rican rum{0.75%oz}, and @dark Jamaican rum{1.5%oz}.
Add @crushed ice{0.5%cup} and flash blend or shake briefly.
Pour unstrained into a #double old-fashioned glass{}.
Garnish with a @mint sprig{1} and a @maraschino cherry{1}.

> [^1]: Berry, *Sippin' Safari* (2017 ed.), Test Pilot chapter — Berry's reconstruction of Donn Beach's c. 1941 Don the Beachcomber spec, including the Pernod / Angostura bitters / falernum signature combination that Donn called "Don's Mix" components.
> [^2]: "Test pilot (cocktail)." Wikipedia. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test_pilot_(cocktail) (accessed 2026-05-03) — secondary-source summary of the c. 1941 Donn Beach attribution and the multiple Berry-recovered variants; cited here as supporting context.
